Defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total sentence of four (4) years.    One (1) year initial confinement, followed by three (3) years extended supervision.   Conditions of extended supervision are:
1) Reimburse Metro Drug Unit for buy money of $110.00;
2) Maintain absolute sobriety; 
3) Maintain full-time employment/schooling combination;
4) Obtain HSED or equivalent;
5) No association with known drug users or dealers;
6) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same;
7) Assessment/treatment/counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process;
8) No presence in any bars or liquor stores;
9) Provide DNA sample;
10) Pay costs of action; 
11) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC.  
Court finds the defendant is not eligible fo rthe Challenge Incarceration Program but is eligible for the Substance Abuse Program.  
$500.00 cash bail is to be returned to poster.  Defendant is given 3 days sentence credit.   
